{"key":"processedPost-10473544","value":{"id":10473544,"first":10473406,"last":10475959,"when":1244514898,"utime":"06/09/09 05:34 AM","content":"The best scale I've found for measuring light is the Kelvin scale.&nbsp; In short, it refers to the color of light that a <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Black_body\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">black body radiator</a> would emit if heated to a certain temperature Celsius.&nbsp; Mushrooms pin and grow best with light in the 5,000K to 7,000K range, thus 7,000 Kelvin is the color you'd see if the metal was heated to 7,000 degrees Celsius.&nbsp; The scale is actually counter-intuitive since the hotter you heat the black body, the 'cooler' the color temperature.&nbsp;  There's more info about lighting at the bottom of the <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Terrarium-Tek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">terrarium tek</a> page on my website.<br />RR","title":"Re: High Frequency Lighting"}}